   "source": [
    "# Wireless Channel Generation for Multiple Carrier Frequencies\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "* In this tutorial, we will analyze the performance of channel Model at multiple carrier frequencies under the propagation scenario Urban Macro or \"UMa\" for a Hexagonal Base Station (BS) Layout.\n",
    "* For a given number of BSs and UEs we generate multi-frequency cluster level channel coefficients corresponding to every link being simulated. \n",
    "\n",
    "* We first import the necessary libraries then followed by creating objects of classes `AntennaArrays`, `NodeMobility`, and `SimulationLayout` respectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "The content of the tutorial is as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Table of Contents**\n",
    "\n",
    "* [Import Libraries](#Import-Libraries)\n",
    "    - [Python Libraries](#Python-Libraries)\n",
    "    - [5G Toolkit Libraries](#5G-Toolkit-Libraries)\n",
    "* [Simulation Parameters](#Simulation-Parameters)\n",
    "* [Generate Antenna Arrays](#Generate-Antenna-Array)\n",
    "* [Node Mobility/Route](#Node-Mobility)\n",
    "* [Generate Simulation Topology](#Generate-Simulation-Layout)\n",
    "* [Generate Channel(LSP/SSPs) Parameters](#Generate-Channel-Parameters)\n",
    "* [Generate Channel Coefficients](#Generate-Channel-Coefficients)\n",
    "* [Generate OFDM Channel Generation](#Generate-OFDM-Channel)\n",
    "    - [Frequency Domain: Magnitude Response Plot](#Frequency-Domain-:-Magnitude-Response-Plot)\n",
    "    - [Time Domain Channel Response](#Time-Domain-Channel-response)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f45b3076",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Import Libraries\n",
    "### Python Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "e991ca9d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "os.environ[\"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES\"] = \"-1\"\n",
    "os.environ['TF_CPP_MIN_LOG_LEVEL'] = '3' \n",
    "\n",
    "# %matplotlib widget\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "import numpy      as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9a042a64",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 5G Toolkit Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "a4d225dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import NodeMobility\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import AntennaArrays\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import SimulationLayout\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import ParameterGenerator\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import ChannelGenerator\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "20cb77ad",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Simulation Parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "The simulation parameters are defined as follows\n",
    "  * ``propTerrain`` defines propagation scenario or terrain for BS-UE, UE-UE, BS-BS links\n",
    "  * ``carrierFrequency`` defines  array of carrier frequencies in GHz\n",
    "  * ``nBSs`` defines number of Base Stations (BSs)\n",
    "  * ``nUEs`` defines number of User Equipments (UEs) \n",
    "  * ``nSnapShots`` defines number of SnapShots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "994a22fc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulation Parameters\n",
    "propTerrain      = \"UMa\"                          # Propagation Scenario or Terrain for BS-UE links\n",
    "carrierFrequency = np.array([3*10**9, 28*10**9])  # Array of two carrier frequencies in Hz\n",
    "nBSs             = 21                             # number of BSs\n",
    "nUEs             = 50                             # number of UEs \n",
    "nSnapShots       = 5                             # number of SnapShots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6bd8db89",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Antenna Array\n",
    "\n",
    "**Antenna Arrays for UEs**\n",
    "\n",
    "The following steps describe the procedure to simulate AntennaArrays Objects at a single carrier frequency\n",
    "both at Tx and Rx side:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "04a4363e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>, <Axes3D: >)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Antenna Array at UE side\n",
    "# assuming antenna element type to be \"OMNI\"\n",
    "# with 2 panel and 2 single polarized antenna element per panel.\n",
    "numCarriers = carrierFrequency.shape[0]\n",
    "ueAntArray  = np.empty(numCarriers, dtype=object)\n",
    "for i in range(carrierFrequency.size):\n",
    "    ueAntArray[i] = AntennaArrays(antennaType     = \"OMNI\", \n",
    "                                  centerFrequency = carrierFrequency[i],\n",
    "                                  arrayStructure  = np.array([1,1,1,2,1]))\n",
    "    ueAntArray[i]() \n",
    "# Radiation Pattern of Rx antenna element \n",
    "ueAntArray[0].displayAntennaRadiationPattern()    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "0cbd67be",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>, <Axes: >)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ueAntArray[0].displayArray(\"2D\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5334b054",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Antenna Arrays for BS**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "2b050e84",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>, <Axes3D: >)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Antenna Array at BS side\n",
    "# assuming antenna element type to be \"3GPP_38.901\", a parabolic antenna \n",
    "# with 4 panel and 4 single polarized antenna element per panel.\n",
    "numCarriers    = carrierFrequency.shape[0]\n",
    "bsAntArray     = np.empty(numCarriers, dtype=object)\n",
    "for i in range(carrierFrequency.size):\n",
    "    bsAntArray[i] = AntennaArrays(antennaType     = \"3GPP_38.901\", \n",
    "                                  centerFrequency = carrierFrequency[i],\n",
    "                                  arrayStructure  = np.array([1,1,2,4,1]))\n",
    "    bsAntArray[i]()\n",
    "# Radiation Pattern of Tx antenna element \n",
    "bsAntArray[0].displayAntennaRadiationPattern()    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "6889bf95",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>, <Axes: >)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bsAntArray[0].displayArray(\"2D\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "edbf47fa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Node Mobility"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d6f8ac47",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This subsection provides the following steps to simulate the mobility of each node"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "e19f87f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>, <Axes: >)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# NodeMobility parameters\n",
    "# assuming that all the BSs are static and all the UEs are mobile.\n",
    "interval = 10*0.5*10**-3/nSnapShots\n",
    "timeInst = np.arange(nSnapShots, dtype=np.float32)*interval  # time values at each snapshot.\n",
    "UEroute  = NodeMobility(\"randomWalk\", nUEs, timeInst, 0, 10)\n",
    "UEroute.displayRoute()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fba3fd70",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Simulation Layout\n",
    "\n",
    "We define the simulation topology parametes:\n",
    "\n",
    " - ``ISD``: Inter Site Distance\n",
    " - ``minDist``: Minimum distance between transmitter and receiver.\n",
    " - ``bsHt``: BS heights \n",
    " - ``ueHt``: UE heights\n",
    " - ``topology``: Simulation Topology\n",
    " - ``nSectorsPerSite``: Number of Sectors Per Site\n",
    " \n",
    "Furthermore, users can access and update following parameters as per their requirements for channel using the handle simLayoutObj.x where x is:\n",
    "\n",
    " - The following parameters can be accessed or updated immendiately after object creation\n",
    "    - ``UEtracks``\n",
    "    - ``UELocations``\n",
    "    - ``ueOrientation``\n",
    "    - ``UEvelocityVector``\n",
    "    - ``BStracks``\n",
    "    - ``BSLocations``\n",
    "    - ``bsOrientation``\n",
    "    - ``BSvelocityVector``\n",
    "    \n",
    " - The following parameters can be accessed or updated after calling the object\n",
    "    - ``linkStateVec``\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "10037fa6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7fa5e98c5110>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Layout Parameters\n",
    "isd                  = 500         # inter site distance\n",
    "minDist              = 35          # min distance between each UE and BS \n",
    "ueHt                 = 1.5         # UE height\n",
    "bsHt                 = 25          # BS height\n",
    "bslayoutType         = \"Hexagonal\" # BS layout type\n",
    "ueDropType           = \"Hexagonal\" # UE drop type\n",
    "nSectorsPerSite      = 3           # number of sectors per site\n",
    "\n",
    "# simulation layout object                                 \n",
    "simLayoutObj = SimulationLayout(numOfBS = nBSs,\n",
    "                                numOfUE = nUEs,\n",
    "                                heightOfBS = bsHt,\n",
    "                                heightOfUE = ueHt,\n",
    "                                UEheightDistribution=\"equal\",\n",
    "                                UEdistibution=\"equal\",\n",
    "                                ISD = isd,\n",
    "                                layoutType = bslayoutType,\n",
    "                                ueDropMethod = ueDropType, \n",
    "                                numOfSectorsPerSite = nSectorsPerSite,\n",
    "                                ueRoute = UEroute) \n",
    "\n",
    "simLayoutObj(terrain = propTerrain,\n",
    "             carrierFreq = carrierFrequency, \n",
    "             ueAntennaArray = ueAntArray,\n",
    "             bsAntennaArray = bsAntArray)\n",
    "\n",
    "# displaying the topology of simulation layout\n",
    "fig, ax = simLayoutObj.display2DTopology()\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"x-coordinates (m)\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"y-coordinates (m)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Simulation Topology\")\n",
    "ax.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6bae9acd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Channel Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "462f957d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* This subsection provides the steps to obtain all the cluster level channel parameters, which includes both `Large Scale Parameters (LSPs)`\n",
    "  and `Small Scale Parameters (SSPs)`. \n",
    "* LSPs includes `Path Loss (PL)`, `Delay Spread (DS)` and `Angular Spreads` both in Azimuth and Zenith directions,\n",
    "  and `cluster powers (Pn)` comes under SSPs.\n",
    "  \n",
    "- LSPs/SSPs: paramGenObj.x where x is\n",
    "    - ``linkStateVec``\n",
    "    - ``delaySpread``\n",
    "    - ``phiAoA_LoS``, ``phiAoA_mn``, ``phiAoA_spread``\n",
    "    - ``thetaAoA_LoS``, ``thetaAoA_mn``, ``thetaAoA_spread``\n",
    "    - ``phiAoD_LoS``, ``phiAoD_mn``, ``phiAoD_spread``\n",
    "    - ``thetaAoD_LoS``, ``thetaAoD_mn``, ``thetaAoD_spread``\n",
    "    - ``xpr``\n",
    "    - ``pathloss``, ``pathDelay``, ``pathPower``\n",
    "    - ``shadowFading``"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "6b416698",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[Warning]: Pathloss model for UMa is defined only for  2D distances 'd2D' between 10m and 5Km! Some distances are from outside this interval!\n",
      "Ignoring for now but might result in unexpected behaviour!\n",
      "[Warning]: Pathloss model for UMa is defined only for  2D distances 'd2D' between 10m and 5Km! Some distances are from outside this interval!\n",
      "Ignoring for now but might result in unexpected behaviour!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# channel parameters\n",
    "paramGenObj = simLayoutObj.getParameterGenerator()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "036ead65",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Channel Coefficients"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e3304b83",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Cluster level channel coefficients can be simulated using the following code snippet.\n",
    "\n",
    " - ``channel.coefficients`` with shape: `(number of carrier frequencies, number of snapshots, number of BSs, number of UEs, numCluster/numPaths, number of Rx antennas, number of Tx antennas)`\n",
    " - ``channel.delays`` with shape: `(number of carrier frequencies, number of snapshots, number of BSs, number of UEs, numCluster/numPaths)`\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "de2ced29",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "channel = paramGenObj.getChannel(applyPathLoss = True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c7d5292a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate OFDM Channel\n",
    "\n",
    "- Shape of OFDM Channel:\n",
    "    - `Hf` is of shape : ``(number of carrier frequencies, number of snapshots, number of BSs, number of UEs, fftsize, number of Rx antennas, number of Tx antennas)``"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7523084c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fftsize           = 512\n",
    "subcarrierSpacing = 15*10**3\n",
    "Hf = channel.ofdm(subcarrierSpacing, fftsize, simLayoutObj.carrierFrequency)\n",
    "# Hf.shape: (numCarrierFrequencies, numSnapShots, numBSs, numUEs, Nfft, numRxAntennas, numTxAntennas)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "61732285",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Frequency Domain : Magnitude Response Plot\n",
    "\n",
    "* The frequency domain magnitude plots (frequency responses) helps demonstate the order of frequency selectivity\n",
    "    - Frequency selectivity is low for LOS Channel\n",
    "    - frequency selectivity is high for NLOS Channels\n",
    "    \n",
    "* Wireless channel at high frequency\n",
    "    - has higher path-loss\n",
    "    - less frequency selective (due to lower delay spread and weak distance paths)\n",
    "    \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a8a29f4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "scaleFig = 1.5\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(17.5/scaleFig,7.5/scaleFig))\n",
    "i = 0\n",
    "ax[0].plot(np.arange(-channel.fftSize/2, channel.fftSize/2)*channel.subCarrierSpacing + channel.fc[0], \n",
    "           np.abs(Hf[0,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"g\", label = \"$f_c$=\"+str(channel.fc[0]/10**9)+\" GHz\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].plot(np.arange(-channel.fftSize/2, channel.fftSize/2)*channel.subCarrierSpacing + channel.fc[1], \n",
    "           np.abs(Hf[1,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"g\", label = \"$f_c$=\"+str(channel.fc[1]/10**9)+\" GHz\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].legend()\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlabel(\"Frequency (Hz)\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel(\"Magnitude Response\")\n",
    "ax[0].grid()\n",
    "ax[1].legend()\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlabel(\"Frequency (Hz)\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylabel(\"Magnitude Response\")\n",
    "ax[1].grid()\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\"Channel Frequency Response at Different Carrier Frequencies\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "92d930c1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Time Domain Channel response\n",
    "\n",
    "- Practical wireless channel are bandlimited which results in:\n",
    "    - impulses widening:\n",
    "        - higher for lower frequency channels\n",
    "    - time spread\n",
    "    \n",
    "These effects can be observed in following plots."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "059ce925",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ht = np.fft.ifft(Hf, fftsize, axis = -3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "9bae3e83",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "scaleFig = 2\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(2,1,figsize=(17.5/scaleFig,17.5/scaleFig))\n",
    "i = 0\n",
    "ax[0].stem(channel.delays[0,0,0,i], np.abs(channel.coefficients[0,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"r\", label = \"Ideal Channel\")\n",
    "ax[0].stem(np.arange(fftsize)/(fftsize*channel.subCarrierSpacing), np.abs(ht[0,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"g\", label = \"Practical Channel\")\n",
    "ax[0].legend()\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlim([0, 0.4*10**-5])\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlabel(\"delays (s)\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel(\"Power\")\n",
    "ax[0].grid()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].stem(channel.delays[1,0,0,i], np.abs(channel.coefficients[1,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"r\", label = \"Ideal Channel\")\n",
    "ax[1].stem(np.arange(fftsize)/(fftsize*channel.subCarrierSpacing), np.abs(ht[1,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"g\", label = \"Practical Channel\")\n",
    "ax[1].legend()\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlim([0, 0.4*10**-5])\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlabel(\"delays (s)\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylabel(\"Power\")\n",
    "ax[1].grid()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\"Power Delay Profile for the Different Carrier Frequencies\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
